{{Infobox language |name=Duan |altname=Halang Doan |states=[[Laos]], [[Vietnam]] |speakers=4,400 |date=1981 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2= [[Bahnaric languages|Bahnaric]] |fam3=[[North Bahnaric languages|North]] |fam4=(unclassified) |iso3=hld |glotto=hala1253 |glottorefname=Halang Doan }}
'''Duan''', '''Doan''', or '''Halang Doan''', is a language spoken by more than four thousand people on either side of the [[Laos|Laotian]]–[[Vietnam]]ese border. There are some 2,346 speakers in [[Attopu Province]], Laos, and another couple of thousand in [[Kon Tum Province]], Vietnam. It is too poorly known to classify completely and may be mutually intelligible with [[Takua language|Takua]], [[Kayong language|Kayong]], [[Halang language|Halang]], and [[Rengao language|Rengao]]. Might be a part of the Xơ Ɖăng ethnic group.
